1 AN ACT relating to the establishment of a grant database.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 ïƒ¢SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 42 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Agency" means any state or local governmental department, cabinet,
7 institution, board, commission, office, or any other unit of government; and
8 (b) "Grant":
9 1. Means money, equipment, material, or services that may be available
10 to an individual or entity from any agency through an application
11 process administered by the agency; and
12 2. Does not include contracts for goods or services an agency obtains
13 through the Kentucky Model Procurement Code, KRS Chapter 45A.
14 (2) The Finance and Administration Cabinet shall establish a grant database that
15 shall serve as a single, unified entry point for individuals and entities to access
16 and review agency grant opportunities. The database shall:
17 (a) Include the ability to use keyword searches to discover all available grant
18 opportunities; and
19 (b) Provide in the information section of the related grant all information
20 reported by agencies as required under subsection (4) of this section.
21 (3) The primary goals of the grant database include:
22 (a) Ensuring state and local grants are easily accessible for individuals and
23 entities of the Commonwealth; and
24 (b) Clearly stating requirements for grants to ensure submissions are qualified
25 for the potential grant.
26 (4) Beginning December 1, 2025, all agencies shall report quarterly to the Finance
27 and Administration Cabinet the grant opportunities that are currently available
